My problem is that primefaces components are not rendered at all. I added the primefaces jar to the WEB-INF/lib folder in the webapp and to the build path, I also did add the xml namespace to my webpage. 

Now something I noticed, that stroke me as weird, is that the primefaces jar is shown twice in the server deployments dropdown [WildFly Deployments screenshot][1], and that the primefaces jar isn&#39;t added to the war structure on my server&#39;s deployment files (it is not in the webapp/WEB-INF/lib) [{war}/WEB-INF/lib directory in WildFly deployment folder screenshot][2]. An other weird thing is that I have a folder called &quot;classes&quot;, that I didn&#39;t add to my structure, inside the {war}/WEB-INF/lib directory (deployments folder) which contains a copy of all of my war&#39;s contents including the primefaces jar I can&#39;t seem to find in the structure I declared. [the &quot;classes&quot; folder (I don&#39;t know where it came from) screenshot][3] [contents of the &quot;classes folder&quot; screenshot][4] [contents of the &quot;WEB-INF/classes/WEB-INF/lib&quot; folder screenshot][5].

An image&#39;s worth a thousand words, check the pics out please and excuse my poor phrasing.

Thanks for the indulgence, hope to have an answer!

